  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The roof extension, by reason of its excessive scale, bulk, detailed design and siting would result in an obtrusive and incompatible form of development which would fail to respect the character and appearance of the subject property and surrounding area nor would it preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the adjacent Lea Bridge Conservation Area. As such, the proposals would be contrary to policies D1 (London’s form, character and capacity for growth), D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) and HC1 (Heritage conservation and growth) of the London Plan (2021), policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the guidance contained with the Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The roof extension, by reason of its height, scale and siting, would result in loss of light and outlook, overbearing impact and increased sense of enclosure which would result in an unacceptable adverse impact on the amenity of the neighbouring occupiers at nos. 202 and 204 Millfields Road. As such the proposed development is contrary to policy D1 (London’s form, character and capacity for growth) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP2 (Development and amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the guidance contained within Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD 2009.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;"
  ],
